        "id": 1000009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-11T00:07:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you\u0027re going to represent the `tag` member as `const char *` then I expect we can omit `tag_length` as you\u0027re stating that `tag` is a valid C string. If it\u0027s not a valid C string (which we should be wary of if it\u0027s pointing into the message buffer) you should use `struct variable_field` instead.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 656,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 657,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "02c2a52e84e2fd77e496501c3c97b75dd316f3cc",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
